cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper discusses the interconnection and coordination of content delivery networks (CDNs) to improve overall service, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the need for scalable and service-oriented architecture, which could be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The topic of QoS and Service Level Agreements (SLAs) could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of closed delivery networks and the need for open content and service delivery networks, which could be related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
